  "description": "Discovery: the 2-byte CID under Service 0x22 is a sliding window into contiguous ECU memory, not an independent reading - byte B of CID N equals byte A of CID N+1 within a real memory block, and the chain breaks cleanly at block boundaries. Verified against the two already-known bitfield groups (1147-1149, 11CC-11CF), where the chain boundaries land exactly where the original decompiled CSVs grouped identifiers together - and revealed 11D0 genuinely extends the 11CC-11CF block by one more byte, undocumented in the CSV. non_trivial_chains lists every chain of 3+ consecutive IDs with non-constant content found across the whole 0x1000-0x12FF nearby range. aliased_content lists byte sequences that repeat at more than one address - some (e.g. 93 00 04 / 80 00 40 / 80 80 80) repeat at exactly 0x29 (41) bytes apart, but checking that period systematically across the whole range only matched ~20.8% of non-zero candidates - real localized pattern, not a confirmed global period.",
